  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Life in Abundance</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to empower young detainees in 4 Cameroonian prisons; Monatel?, Mfou, Ngoumou and Bagangte. The project improves the socioeconomic living conditions of young detainees by providing them with legal assistance, vocational and educational training, creating contact with their families and giving psychological support. This equips the young detainees with skills beneficial and necessary for their current situation as well as for their lives after release. Thus, the project wishes to not only create hope but independence, and dignity among the young detainees in order to provide them with the feeling of being actors and not only bystanders in their own lives. The long-term goal of the project is to improve socialization and reduce recidivism after release and by promoting overall advocacy on various levels, the project seeks to create greater awareness of detainees? often unrighteous and appalling conditions.</narrative>
  </description>
